elephant, tiger, rhinoceros, tibetan antelope and snow lotus decimated or on the verge of extinction. the city of pingyao and several markets on the outskirts of beijing are notorious for selling rare animal skins, furs, claws, horns, skulls, bones, and other parts from endangered (even extinct) species. anyone purchasing such items is encouraging the further destruction of the species in question. it is illegal to trade in such products in nearly all countries, including china, under the convention on international trade in endangered species. enforcement in china is somewhat lax, but anyone buying such products risks serious hassles either when 